 [je crois qu'il y a des refs sur les effets non-monotone des interactions
 +, je rechercherai]).
 The predator effects that we highlighted above can be comprised within
 such niche differentation sensu largo: specialized predators can make strong
 conspecific density-dependence emerge [REFs], while switching generalists
 can also promote diversity [REFs, same from Oikos].
 Both predators and resources have often symmetrical effects and can contribute
 to niche differentation [REF to Chesson 2018 J Ecol]
